# Monday MCP Tool Preference

## Patterns to Flag

- `fetch`, `axios`, or `requests` calls targeting `https://api.monday.com` or `api.monday.com`
- `graphql-request` or similar clients posting directly to the Monday GraphQL endpoint from editor-bound code
- Raw HTTP `POST` bodies with Monday API tokens to `v2` GraphQL when a first-party MCP tool covers the same operation

## What to Do

- Prefer Monday MCP tools in Cursor: `get_board_info`, `get_board_items_page`, `create_item`, `change_item_column_values`, `all_monday_api`, and others listed in the plugin docs for the matching operation
- Use `all_monday_api` only when no dedicated tool exists or for one-off advanced queries still reviewed for complexity and pagination
- Keep API tokens in MCP / environment configuration the host provides, not duplicated in ad-hoc scripts unless necessary for non-Cursor automation

## Exceptions

- Standalone CLIs, servers, or CI jobs that do not run inside Cursor (no MCP available)
- Official Monday SDKs used in deployed services where MCP is not in the execution path
- Code comments or docs referencing example HTTP shapes without executing requests
